
[1]patriotism

   PAT'RIOTISM ,n. Love of one's country; the passion which aims to serve
   one's country, either in defending it from invasion, or protecting its
   rights and maintaining its laws and institutions in vigor and purity.
   Patriotism is the characteristic of a good citizen, the noblest passion
   that animates a man in the character of a citizen.
